When you use iTunes to create an audio CD from a playlist, it is burned using industry standard CD-A formatting so will be playable on any CD and most DVD players. However, due to fundamental differences in the way DVDs are structured, and the way disc burning software and DVD players work, you cannot put CD-A recordings on to a blank DVD. If you want to put your playlist, or lot of music files onto a blank DVD it has to be in the form of a data disc, and if the music files are in mp3 format, then they may be playable on some, though by no means all DVD players.
